.TH DBX-SMITH-RM 1 "April 2026" "DbxSmith" "User Manual"
.SH NAME
dbx-smith-rm \- Atomic destructor for Distrobox containers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dbx-smith-rm
[options] <box_name>
.br

.B --help/-h:
show this help message
.br
.B --purge/-p:
Deep clean: Purge container, isolated home dir, registry manifest, shortcut fragments, isolated network bridges, and internal Podman volumes.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dbx-smith-rm
is the atomic destructor for Distrobox containers and their associated DbxSmith infrastructure. It ensures that when a container is removed, all corresponding artifacts—such as isolated home directories, shell aliases, registry manifests, network bridges, and podman volumes—are cleanly purged from the host system.
.SH EXAMPLES
Remove a container and its basic configuration:
.br

	dbx-smith-rm my-alpine
.br

Perform a deep purge of a container, including all volumes and network bridges:
.br

	dbx-smith-rm \--purge my-vault
